Python Arrays

Python’s usual “array” for homework and scripts is the list: ordered, mutable.

The array module (import array) stores compact numeric arrays (typecodes like 'i', 'f').
For heavy numeric work, libraries like NumPy are common (separate tutorial).

W3Schools introduces list-style operations under “Arrays”; practice with list.

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_arrays.asp
